com.pholser.junit.quickcheck

Annotation Type Property


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Property

    Mark a method on a class that is run with the JUnitQuickcheck runner with this annotation to have it run as a property-based test.

    A method marked with this annotation should be an instance method declared as public with a return type of void.

    • Element Detail

      • trials

        public abstract int trials
        Returns:
        how many sets of parameters to verify the property with
        Default:
        100

      • shrink

        public abstract boolean shrink
        Returns:
        whether or not to attempt to shrink a failing set of parameters
        Default:
        true

      • maxShrinks

        public abstract int maxShrinks
        Returns:
        the maximum number of shrink attempts to make on a failing set of parameters; in effect only when shrink() is true
        Default:
        100

      • maxShrinkDepth

        public abstract int maxShrinkDepth
        Returns:
        the maximum depth of shrink tree to make on a failing set of parameters; in effect only when shrink() is true
        Default:
        20

      • maxShrinkTime

        public abstract int maxShrinkTime
        Returns:
        the maximum elapsed time for the shrinking process in milliseconds; in effect only when shrink() is true
        Default:
        60000

      • onMinimalCounterexample

        public abstract Class<? extends MinimalCounterexampleHook> onMinimalCounterexample
        Returns:
        callback that it is executed if a minimal counterexample is found (after shrinking)
        Default:
        com.pholser.junit.quickcheck.hook.NilMinimalCounterexampleHook.class
